    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of medium-sized oak tree with a round crown native to the southeastern United States, but found from New York to Florida, Missouri, and Texas. It is a timber tree, and the bark is a source of tannin. It may occasionally form hybrids with other red oaks in the region.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
